<div class="page">
  <div class="pagenum">第 1 頁<br>共 11 頁</div>
  <div class="subinfo">
    114年學測<br>英文考科
  </div>
  <div class="content-area">
    <div class="important" style="margin-top:4px;margin-bottom:18px;">
      請記得在答題卷簽名欄位以正楷簽全名
    </div>
    <div class="section-title">第壹部分、選擇題（占62分）</div>
    <div class="q-title">一、詞彙題（占10分）</div>
    <div class="q-desc">
      說明：第1題至第10題為單選題，每題1分。
    </div>
    <ol class="q-list" start="1">
      <li>When you walk on the sandy beach, your footprints will ______ after the waves wash over them.<br>
        (A) vanish &nbsp; (B) expand &nbsp; (C) rotate &nbsp; (D) deposit</li>
      <li>The city government plans to promote ______ transportation to reduce air pollution.<br>
        (A) electric &nbsp; (B) personal &nbsp; (C) digital &nbsp; (D) ancient</li>
      <li>Many workers are ______ about the upcoming changes in the company's policies.<br>
        (A) delighted &nbsp; (B) anxious &nbsp; (C) skillful &nbsp; (D) grateful</li>
      <li>This museum is ______ for its collection of ancient artifacts and rare paintings.<br>
        (A) famous &nbsp; (B) instant &nbsp; (C) random &nbsp; (D) private</li>
      <li>The new employee quickly ______ herself with her colleagues by being friendly and helpful.<br>
        (A) measured &nbsp; (B) associated &nbsp; (C) impressed &nbsp; (D) integrated</li>
      <li>The team leader gave ______ instructions before the competition began.<br>
        (A) vague &nbsp; (B) precise &nbsp; (C) patient &nbsp; (D) remote</li>
      <li>Tourists are ______ to follow the rules when visiting the historic monument.<br>
        (A) required &nbsp; (B) prevented &nbsp; (C) ignored &nbsp; (D) confused</li>
      <li>After the repair, the machine now operates more ______ than before.<br>
        (A) secretly &nbsp; (B) efficiently &nbsp; (C) severely &nbsp; (D) rarely</li>
      <li>The little boy was ______ by the magician's amazing tricks.<br>
        (A) inspired &nbsp; (B) educated &nbsp; (C) fascinated &nbsp; (D) replaced</li>
      <li>During the storm, the power ______ in several neighborhoods for hours.<br>
        (A) remained &nbsp; (B) supplied &nbsp; (C) exploded &nbsp; (D) failed</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>

