  <div class="content-area">
    <div class="q-title">二、綜合測驗（占10分）</div>
    <div class="q-desc">
      說明：第11題至第20題為單選題，每題1分。
    </div>
    <div class="q-desc" style="font-size:17px;color:#222;margin-bottom:7px;">
      第11至15題為題組
    </div>
    <div class="passage">
      In a small town in Italy, there is a tradition called "La Festa della Primavera." Every year, people gather in the main square to welcome the arrival of spring. The celebration begins with a parade, during which children throw flower petals into the air, creating a colorful scene. Later, everyone enjoys traditional food and music together. The festival is so lively that it ______ 11 ______ both locals and tourists.
    </div>
    <ol class="q-list" start="11">
      <li>(A) attracts &nbsp; (B) ignores &nbsp; (C) examines &nbsp; (D) repairs</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="passage">
      The origins of this festival date back several centuries. According to local legend, villagers once held the event to ______ 12 ______ the end of a harsh winter. Over time, the tradition has become an important part of the community. Today, families ______ 13 ______ to prepare costumes and practice songs for the big day.
    </div>
    <ol class="q-list" start="12">
      <li>(A) celebrate &nbsp; (B) postpone &nbsp; (C) disturb &nbsp; (D) prevent</li>
      <li>(A) refuse &nbsp; (B) gather &nbsp; (C) abandon &nbsp; (D) hesitate</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="passage">
      This joyful occasion ______ 14 ______ the spirit of unity among the townspeople. Many visitors say it's an experience they will never forget, as the festival ______ 15 ______ lasting memories for all who attend.
    </div>
    <ol class="q-list" start="14">
      <li>(A) destroys &nbsp; (B) strengthens &nbsp; (C) confuses &nbsp; (D) limits</li>
      <li>(A) forgets &nbsp; (B) creates &nbsp; (C) misses &nbsp; (D) doubts</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="q-desc" style="font-size:17px;color:#222;margin:20px 0 7px 0;">
      第16至20題為題組
    </div>
    <div class="passage">
      Sarah had always dreamed of becoming a chef. She spent many hours in the kitchen, trying out new recipes and learning different cooking techniques. However, her first attempt at baking a cake was a disaster. The mixture ______ 16 ______ in the oven, and the cake came out flat and tasteless.
    </div>
    <ol class="q-list" start="16">
      <li>(A) succeeded &nbsp; (B) failed &nbsp; (C) melted &nbsp; (D) floated</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>

