    </ol>

    <div class="q-title" style="margin-top:25px;">五、閱讀測驗（占24分）</div>
    <div class="q-desc">
      說明：第35題至第46題為單選題，每題2分。
    </div>
    <div class="q-desc" style="font-size:17px;color:#222;margin-bottom:7px;">
      第35至38題為題組
    </div>
    <div class="passage">
      Have you ever wondered how dogs became "man's best friend"? Scientists believe that thousands of years ago, wild wolves began to live near human settlements. Early humans left food scraps behind, and the friendlier wolves stayed close to take advantage of this. Over many generations, these wolves became less aggressive and more comfortable around people.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Page 6 -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="pagenum">第 6 頁<br>共 11 頁</div>
  <div class="subinfo">
    114年學測<br>英文考科
  </div>
  <div class="content-area">
    <div class="passage">
      Eventually, humans realized the benefits of having wolves nearby, such as protection and assistance in hunting. Through careful selection, people began to breed wolves that showed gentle behaviors. This process led to the domestication of dogs.
    </div>
    <div class="passage">
      Today, dogs are valued not only as pets but also as helpers in many fields, including search and rescue, therapy, and law enforcement. New research continues to uncover the fascinating history behind our relationship with these loyal animals.
    </div>
    <ol class="q-list" start="35">
      <li>What is the main purpose of this passage?<br>
        (A) To explain how dogs were trained to hunt.<br>
        (B) To describe the process of dog domestication.<br>
        (C) To show the dangers of wild animals.<br>
        (D) To discuss modern uses of dogs.</li>
      <li>According to the passage, why did early wolves stay near humans?<br>
        (A) They wanted to protect people.<br>
        (B) They were attracted by food.<br>
        (C) They were looking for shelter.<br>
        (D) They needed to learn new skills.</li>
      <li>What does "domestication" mean in the context of the passage?<br>
        (A) Feeding wild animals.<br>
        (B) Keeping animals in zoos.<br>
        (C) Taming animals for human use.<br>
        (D) Training animals to hunt.</li>
      <li>Which of the following is NOT mentioned as a modern role of dogs?<br>
        (A) Law enforcement<br>
        (B) Therapy<br>
        (C) Surgery<br>
        (D) Search and rescue</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="q-desc" style="font-size:17px;color:#222;margin:20px 0 7px 0;">
      第39至42題為題組
    </div>
    <div class="passage">
      The Eiffel Tower is one of the most famous landmarks in the world. Built in 1889 for the Paris World's Fair, it was originally intended to be a temporary structure. Many Parisians disliked its design at first, calling it an eyesore. However, the tower quickly became a symbol of Paris and is now a popular tourist attraction, drawing millions of visitors each year.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

