      Plastic pollution is a growing problem for our planet. Every year, millions of tons of plastic waste end up in the oceans, harming marine life and damaging ecosystems. Many animals, such as turtles and seabirds, mistake plastic for food and can become sick or die after eating it.
    </div>
    <div class="passage">
      Governments and organizations around the world are working to reduce plastic pollution. Some countries have banned single-use plastics, while others promote recycling and encourage people to use reusable bags and containers.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Page 8 -->
<div class="page">
