    <div class="passage">
      However, solving this problem requires cooperation from everyone. By making small changes in our daily lives, such as refusing plastic straws and bottles, we can all help protect the environment.
    </div>
    <ol class="q-list" start="43">
      <li>What is the main problem discussed in the passage?<br>
        (A) Air pollution<br>
        (B) Plastic waste in the oceans<br>
        (C) Deforestation<br>
        (D) Noise pollution</li>
      <li>According to the passage, how does plastic pollution affect animals?<br>
        (A) It makes them stronger.<br>
        (B) It helps them find food.<br>
        (C) It can make them sick or kill them.<br>
        (D) It improves their health.</li>
      <li>What are some solutions mentioned in the passage?<br>
        (A) Burning all plastic waste<br>
        (B) Using more single-use plastics<br>
        (C) Recycling and using reusable items<br>
        (D) Ignoring the problem</li>
      <li>What is the main message of the passage?<br>
        (A) Only governments can solve environmental issues.<br>
        (B) Everyone can help reduce plastic pollution.<br>
        (C) Plastic is not harmful to the environment.<br>
        (D) Marine animals are not affected by plastic.</li>
    </ol>

